messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full HTTP request path:
- /api/paste

HTTP methods (based strictly on the code annotations, not on framework defaults):

- All methods acceptable: false
- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: false
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The controller class is annotated with @RequestMapping("/api/paste"), so the base path is /api/paste.
- A method is annotated with @PostMapping with no path attribute, which maps POST requests to the class-level path -> POST /api/paste (hence POST = true).
- There are @GetMapping and @DeleteMapping methods, but they map to subpaths: @GetMapping(path = "/{paste_id}") and @DeleteMapping(path = "/{paste_id}") and @GetMapping(path = "/public"). Those do not map GET or DELETE to the exact base path /api/paste, so GET and DELETE are false for /api/paste itself.
- No method in this controller explicitly maps HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, PUT, PATCH, or a wildcard/all-methods mapping, so those are false when judged strictly from the source code annotations.
